        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 3:17PM CDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 316 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles northwest of Norton, moving north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern Norton
County, including the following locations... Reager.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
